"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-06-seine-water-quality-improves-ahead-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - The water quality of the Seine has improved, test results showed on Thursday, three weeks ahead of the start of the Paris Olympics when the river is set to host outdoor swimming events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.949935281651079, \"rank\": 0.03610028619848912, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 47, \"end\": 52, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"The water quality\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"test results\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 79}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 90, \"to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 130}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 152}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 167}, {\"ngram\": \"outdoor swimming events\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Results published by the Paris mayor's office showed that E. coli bacteria levels at an Olympics swimming spot in central Paris had fallen to within acceptable limits for four days in a row, following warm and sunny weather in the French capital.\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 440, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8190211032204686, \"rank\": 0.17958448176154404, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Results\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 216}, {\"ngram\": \"E. coli bacteria levels\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics swimming spot\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"acceptable limits\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"four days\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"warm and sunny weather\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This positive development is a consequence of the return of sunshine and warmth as well as the effects of the work done as part of the strategy to improve the quality of the Seine's waters,\\\" a statement from the mayor's office said.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This positive development\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"a consequence\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"the return\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"sunshine\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"warmth\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"the effects\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"the strategy\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor's office\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The previous week, levels of E. coli - a bacteria indicating the presence of faecal matter - had been above the upper limits used by sports federations every day at Alexandre III bridge in central Paris, which is set to be the jumping off point for the swimming.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"levels\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"E. coli\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"a bacteria\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"faecal matter\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"the upper limits\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"sports federations\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"Alexandre III bridge\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"point\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point, E. coli levels were 10 times the upper limit of 1,000 colony-forming units per 100 millilitres (cfu/ml), with heavy rain in previous days blamed for a spike in untreated sewage in the waterway.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"E. coli levels\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"10 times the upper limit\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"1,000 colony-forming units\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"100 millilitres\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"cfu/ml\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rain\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"previous days\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"a spike\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"untreated sewage\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"the waterway\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine is set to be used for the swimming leg of the triathlon on July 30-31 and August 5, as well as the open-water swimming on August 8-9.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the swimming leg\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"the open-water swimming\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The readings for enterococci bacteria last week - a second key measurement of water quality - also improved markedly and were within acceptable limits every day at Alexandre III bridge.\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The readings\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1322}, {\"ngram\": \"enterococci bacteria\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"a second key measurement\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1384}, {\"ngram\": \"water quality\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"acceptable limits\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"Alexandre III bridge\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera hailed a \\\"clear improvement in the water of the Seine's waters\\\" and said the readings \\\"enable us to envisage the competitions going ahead serenely\\\".\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1582, \"end\": 1587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"clear improvement\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"the readings\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitions\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French authorities have spent 1.4 billion euros (US$1.5 billion) in the last decade trying to clean up the river by improving the Paris sewerage system, as well as building new water treatment and storage facilities.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1684, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8190211032204686, \"rank\": 0.17958448176154404, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"1.4 billion euros\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"the last decade\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"new water treatment and storage facilities\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But major storms still overwhelm the capital's waste water network, some of which date back to the 19th century, leading to discharges of effluent directly into the Seine.\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2067, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"major storms\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's waste water network\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"date\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the 19th century\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2013}, {\"ngram\": \"discharges\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The period for the latest results covered June 24-July 2, and the mayor's office said that the river was swimmable for six out of the nine days in total over the period \\\"at almost all\\\" of the four spots it took samples from.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2299, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The period\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"the latest results\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"-July\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor's office\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"the nine days\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"the period\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2243}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"the four spots\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"samples\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the start of the year Paris has had 415 mm (16 inches) of rainfall, around 40 per cent above the long-term average according to the French weather office.\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2329, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8190211032204686, \"rank\": 0.17958448176154404, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"415 mm\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2349}, {\"ngram\": \"16 inches\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"rainfall\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"the long-term average\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Frequent rain storms in May and June have not only led to pollution problems but have also increased the flow and height of the river, causing different problems for organisers .\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2641, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Frequent rain storms\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2499}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution problems\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2539}, {\"ngram\": \"the flow\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"height\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"different problems\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2624}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rehearsals for the water-borne opening ceremony, which is set to take place on the river Seine on July 26, have had to be repeatedly postponed because of the strength of the currents.\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rehearsals\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"the water-borne opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2690}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2718}, {\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2737}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2745}, {\"ngram\": \"the strength\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"the currents\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine's flow last week ranged between 400-600 m3/second - many times above the usual level for this time of year of around 100-150 m3/s.\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"400-600 m3/second - many times\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2900}, {\"ngram\": \"the usual level\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"this time\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2936}, {\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"around 100-150 m3\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What we need to avoid is it going above 500 m3/s,\\\" the director in charge of Paris Olympic ceremonies, Thierry Reboul, toldAFPon Thursday.\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 3109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3048, \"end\": 3053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.815991272085885e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3074, \"end\": 3081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.127546369526809e-20, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"500 m3/s\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3019}, {\"ngram\": \"the director\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3034}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3044}, {\"ngram\": \"toldAFPon\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currents at their present levels could also lead to the cancellation of the swimming for safety reasons.\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Currents\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3119}, {\"ngram\": \"their present levels\", \"from\": 3123, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"the cancellation\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"safety reasons\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the weather improves \\\"it's possible to return to the usual flow for this time of year quite quickly\\\", the organisation in charge of managing upstream reservoirs on the Seine, Seine Grands Lacs, toldAFP.\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3395, \"end\": 3400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999967380973, \"rank\": 3.2617550481126648e-